        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: add Clawcks install option",
        "body": "﻿## Summary\n- Add a Clawcks install page.\n- Add Clawcks to the install hosting list.\n- Add the new page to docs navigation.\n- Add explicit third-party credential trust wording before setup steps.\n- Clarify that the OpenAI API key is only needed for onboarding and users can switch providers or harnesses after setup.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nPeople choosing where to run OpenClaw cannot currently find Clawcks in the install docs. The install overview lists other hosting options, but Clawcks has no page or navigation entry.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThis adds a requested, neutral docs page for Clawcks as an opinionated hosted OpenClaw option. The page also makes the third-party credential trust boundary explicit before onboarding and deploy steps.\n\nThe change is limited to install docs, docs navigation, and the i18n glossary entry for the Clawcks brand name. It does not change runtime behavior, installer behavior, or config.\n\n## User Impact\nUsers can now discover Clawcks from the install overview, see that Clawcks is independent from OpenClaw, understand that Clawcks handles entered credentials as the hosted Gateway operator, and decide whether hosted Clawcks setup fits better than managing their own server, container, network, filesystem, and deployment process.\n\nThe page also clarifies that the OpenAI API key is needed for onboarding, and that users can switch OpenClaw to any supported model provider and any supported agent harness, including Codex, after setup.\n\n## Evidence\nThe new page appears in the docs index, internal links resolve, credential-trust wording appears before the prerequisites/deploy handoff, and the touched docs pass formatting and whitespace checks. CI `check-docs` and `Real behavior proof` were green before the latest docs-only review update; new CI is running on the pushed commit.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm docs:check-links`\n- `pnpm docs:check-i18n-glossary`\n- `oxfmt --check` on touched docs\n- `git diff --check`\r\n",
